title: ACT's first coronavirus death was a Ruby Princess passenger
description: ACT Health was initially reluctant to release personal details about the woman, in her 80s, who died at Canberra Hospital over the weekend, other than to say she was an international traveller.
content:
Posted 
March 31, 2020 14:25:54
The first person in the ACT to die from COVID-19 was a passenger on the Ruby Princess cruise ship, authorities have confirmed at the request of her family.
